# Changelog - EPICS Major Mode for Emacs
## [0.6.1] - 2021.07.13
### Added
- Functions for adding and removing records
- Function that checks the contents of a nearby line
### Removed
- Working with snippets proved to be cumbersome to work with.
Additionally, it proved difficult to provide sane default. This functionality is thus removed
and replaced by simpler functions for adding and removing records.
## [0.6.0] - 2021.03.18
### Added
- Functions and commands for creating, editing and saving snippets
- epics-var-dir where persistent variables are saved
### Fixed
- Updated mode description
- Some docstrings were missing type information
### Changed
- Fixed inconsistent mode naming

## [0.5.1] - 2021.02.04
### Added
- epics-next-record and epics-previous-record commands facilitate navigation between record blocks
- epics-next-value and epics-previous-value facilitate navigation between values
- A lot of internal utility functions
### Fixed
- Some themes were not completely compatible with syntax colouring

## [0.5.0] - 2021.01.06
### Added
- epics-path-to-base customization variable
- epics-describe-record opens a corresponding reference in a help buffer
- epics-open-reference prompts for the desired reference
### Changed
- Change CL "equalp" predicate with elisp "equal"
- Refactored and improve many internal functions
- Finally updated the README

## [0.4.2] - 2020.09.10
### Added
- Functions for following links

## [0.4.1] - 2020.08.16
### Added
- Customisation group, only for setting number of indentation spaces
### Fixed
- Indentation function should not do anything if already at desired indent (to preserve undo history)

## [0.4.0] - 2020.08.14
### Added
- Basic indentation calculation functions
### Changed
- Dehardcoded keywords

## [0.3.1] - 2020.03.20
### Changed
- Improve asyn regex to allow multiple macros
- Separate asyn and streamdevice regexes

## [0.3.0] - 2020.03.16
### Added
- Finish adding epics keywords for menuChoices, stream and asyn dtypes

### Changed
- menu-choices are now refered to as keywords

## [0.2.2] - 2020.03.12
### Added
- Autoload for .db, .dbd, .template files
- LICENCE file
- MSS to epics-link-params

## Changed
- Reverse regex order, so syntax colors correctly
- Change mode name to 'EPICS'

## [0.2.1] - 2020.03.09
### Fixed
- MenuChoices syntax coloring should not color quotation marks

## [0.2.0] - 2020.03.09
### Changed
- MenuChoices are now highlighted

## [0.1.1] - 2020.03.05
### Added
- Highlighting for CA, CPP, CP, NPP, PP, NMS and MS
- comment-dwim functionality
- README.md

## [0.1.0] - 2020.03.01
### Added
- Different highlighting of records if they are input, output or general
- Highlighting of input and output fields, some fields related to scanning, alarm fields
- Comment, macro and string highlighting
